cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.AR, cs.MM

The paper discusses the integration of satellite and terrestrial networks for extending broadband coverage, which involves network infrastructure, communication protocols, and signal processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also addresses the impact of satellite channel impairments on LTE PHY/MAC procedures, which involves information theory and signal processing, making cs.IT (Information Theory) another likely category. The paper proposes two architectures for a LEO mega-constellation realizing a satellite-enabled LTE system, which involves system design and control, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) another likely category. The paper also discusses the technical challenges of integrating satellite and terrestrial networks, which involves architecture and algorithms, making cs.AR (Architecture) another likely category. Finally, the paper discusses the impact of satellite channel impairments on handover procedures, which involves multimedia systems and human-computer interaction, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a less likely but still possible category.
